qHHos422Z6Nj14AwZP_V_yy_zwzqI-hPjXB6fO4dH9OK3Fox_Q ) PC sales shot through =
the roof during the pandemic, but a lot of those sales pulled forward growt=
h, leaving a big hangover. That said, I actually thought that Microsoft=E2=
=80=99s commentary on the PC market was pretty encouraging on two fronts.

First, from CFO Amy Hood on the earnings call ( https://seekingalpha.com/ar=
ticle/4572123-microsoft-corporation-msft-q2-2023-earnings-call-transcript )=
 :

In More Personal Computing, we expect revenue of $11.9 billion to $12.3 bil=
lion. Windows OEM revenue should decline in the mid to high 30s, in line wi=
th the PC market. We expect Q3 PC units to be similar to pre-pandemic level=
s.

That=E2=80=99s a pretty big drop:

At the same time, given that More Personal Computing was declining up to ar=
ound 2017, beating pre-pandemic quarters isn=E2=80=99t too shabby. Not all =
of More Personal Computing is PCs, of course: the division includes devices=
, gaming, and search and news advertising. Still, Xbox doesn=E2=80=99t have=
 any original games on the docket, and advertising is depressed, so all-in-=
all that=E2=80=99s a better forecast than I would have expected. CEO Satya =
Nadella gave a clue as to why this might be the case in his prepared remark=
s:

While the number of PCs shipped declined during the quarter, returning to p=
re-pandemic levels, usage intensity of Windows continues to be higher than =
pre-pandemic with time spent per PC up nearly 10%. Monthly active devices a=
lso reached an all-time high this quarter.

Intel made the case earlier this month ( https://www.intc.com/news-events/i=
r-calendar/detail/20230112-pc-tam-and-platform-roadmap-investor-webinar ) t=
hat the PC market had permanently increased thanks to COVID: yes, sales wer=
e pulled forward, but more people realized the value of PCs while being stu=
ck at home, and would buy more PCs more frequently going forward. This pred=
iction was panned a bit, given how self-serving it was, particularly given =
Intel=E2=80=99s current struggles. Nadella=E2=80=99s data point about time =
spent, though, along with the bad-but-not-as-bad-as-I-expected forecast for=
 PC growth suggests there might be something to this.

Azure=E2=80=99s Slowdown
----------------

The biggest news in terms of Microsoft=E2=80=99s stock, though, was Azure; =
Hood reported:

Next, the Intelligent Cloud segment. Revenue was $21.5 billion, increasing =
18% and 24% in constant currency, in line with expectations. Overall, serve=
r products and cloud services revenue increased 20% and 26% in constant cur=
rency. Azure and other cloud services revenue grew 31% and 38% in constant =
currency. As noted earlier, growth continued to moderate, particularly in D=
ecember, and we exited the quarter with Azure constant currency growth in t=
he mid-30s.

As for the forecast:

As I noted earlier, we exited Q2 with Azure growth in the mid-30s in consta=
nt currency. And from that, we expect Q3 growth to decelerate roughly 4 to =
5 points in constant currency.

I only highlight this because I found this exchange in the Q&A portion of t=
he call humorous:

*When you talk about a 4-point to 5-point decel in Azure, that=E2=80=99s of=
f of the 38% reported for December, right, not off the 35% exit rate? Thank=
 you.*

=E2=80=A6On the second half of your question, which is the guide of the exi=
t rate =E2=80=93 it=E2=80=99s off the exit rate on Azure of four points to =
five points, just to make sure that is clear.

Needless to say, analysts really wanted to believe the opposite! After all,=
 Microsoft had delivered impressive Azure growth last quarter while AWS str=
uggled. I suspect, though, that Microsoft is simply feeling the same pain A=
WS did on a delayed basis. First off, with regards to the nature of the pai=
n, I wrote this after Microsoft and Amazon=E2=80=99s earnings last quarter =
( https://stratechery.com/2022/meta-ai-infrastructure-spend-microsoft-and-a=
mazon-earnings-paying-the-promise-of-cloud-computing/?access_token=3DeyJhbG=
